  "prompt": "What does the phrase \"As a token of appreciation\" mean?",
  "response": "The phrase **\"As a token of appreciation\"** is used to express gratitude or thanks by giving someone a small gift, gesture, or symbolic item. It signifies that the gesture or item is a representation of one\u2019s appreciation, even if it\u2019s modest or simple.  \n\nFor example:  \n- \"As a token of appreciation, please accept this gift card for your hard work.\"  \n- \"We\u2019d like to give you this certificate as a token of our appreciation for your support.\"  \n\nIt emphasizes that the act or item is a thoughtful way to show gratitude, even if it\u2019s not grand or overly significant.",
